  <h3>Vanilla Bean Sugar Cookies</h3>
<div class="row">  
  <ul class="col-6">
   <li>1/3 Cp Butter</li><li>3/4 Cp Granulated Sugar</li>
   <li>1/3 Cp Shortening</li><li>1 Tbsp Milk</li>
   <li>2 Cps Flour</li><li>1 Tsp Baking Powder</li>
   <li>1 Egg</li><li>1/8 Tsp Salt</li>
   <li>1 Real Vanilla Bean </li>
  </ul> 
  
    <div class="col-6">
      <!--<%= image_tag 'Sugarcookies.png', class: 'img-fluid' %>-->
    </div>
  </div>  
 Combined butter, shortening, egg, milk, and vanilla together and set aside. Combine flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, and salt together and blend well. Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. Chill dough for 3 hrs 
 Preheat oven to 375 degrees and bake for 7-8 minutes. Place balls approximately 2 inch think on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar before baking unless you plan to ice your cookies.
